naccurate.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20noted%20that%20Claude's%20high%20refusal%20rates%20risked%20limiting%20its%20utility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHallucinations%20persist%20due%20to%20the%20way%20most%20evaluations%20are%20graded%20%E2%80%94%20language%20models%20are%20optimized%20to%20be%20good%20test-takers%2C%20and%20guessing%20when%20uncertain%20improves%20test%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote%20in%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flimits-large-language-models-chatgpt-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-openai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELarge%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20essentially%20always%20in%20%26quot%3Btest-taking%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20answering%20questions%20as%20if%20everything%20in%20life%20were%20binary%20%E2%80%94%20right%20or%20wrong%2C%20black%20or%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20they're%20not%20equipped%20for%20the%20realities%20of%20life%2C%20where%20uncertainty%20is%20more%20common%20than%20certainty%2C%20and%20true%20accuracy%20is%20not%20a%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHumans%20learn%20the%20value%20of%20expressing%20uncertainty%20outside%20of%20school%2C%20in%20the%20school%20of%20hard%20knocks.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20language%20models%20are%20primarily%20evaluated%20using%20exams%20that%20penalize%20uncertainty%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20fix%2C%20and%20it%20has%20to%20do%20with%20redesigning%20evaluation%20metrics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20root%20problem%20is%20the%20abundance%20of%20evaluations%20that%20are%20not%20aligned%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20numerous%20primary%20evaluations%20must%20be%20adjusted%20to%20stop%20penalizing%20abstentions%20when%20uncertain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20blog%20post%20about%20the%20paper%2C%20OpenAI%20elaborated%20on%20what%20this%20type%20of%20adjustment%20would%20en