EHe%20argues%20that%20every%20child%20is%20inherently%20motivated%20to%20grow%20and%20that%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20offer%20them%20a%20reward%20to%20walk%20or%20talk%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20do%20the%20same%20for%20any%20other%20task.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20reflects%20on%20whether%20we%20need%20to%20put%20children%20in%20so%20many%20classes%20and%20if%20they%20really%20enjoy%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20to%20give%20our%20child%20the%20space%20to%20find%20what%20they%20like.%20We%20need%20to%20give%20them%20exposure%20to%20understand%20what%20they%20like.%20It%20has%20taken%20me%2040%20years%20to%20come%20to%20a%20place%20where%20I%E2%80%99m%20doing%20something%20I%20love.%20I%20am%20internally%20motivated%20today%2C%20nobody%20is%20pushing%20me.%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20doing%20it%20for%20fame%2C%20money%20or%20external%20validation.%20I%E2%80%99m%20doing%20it%20because%20I%20love%20doing%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarpreet%20points%20out%20that%20we%20need%20to%20teach%20children%20to%20regulate%20their%20emotions.%20Hitting%20obviously%20is%20not%20the%20right%20way%20to%20do%20it%2C%20nor%20is%20propping%20them%20up%20before%20a%20screen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20they%20are%2030%20and%20angry%2C%20are%20they%20going%20to%20see%20a%20screen%20and%20pacify%20themselves%3F%20We%20should%20not%20teach%20children%20to%20distract%20themselves%20because%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20help%20them%20process%20their%20emotions.%20Just%20because%20we%20weren%E2%80%99t%20taught%20this%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20we%20should%20repeat%20it%20with%20the%20next%20generation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20a%20child%20is%20watching%20a%20screen%2C%20they%20are%20not%20involved%20in%20anything%20around%20them.%20That%20is%20the%20core%20issue%20which%20leads%20to%20many%20mental%20health%20problems.%20To%20prevent