%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F371845%2Fadhd-at-workplace-employee-journey-with-adhd-in-his-career-tips-to-manage-inattention-distraction-symptoms%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enormalises%20her%20son%E2%80%99s%20ADHD%20both%20at%20home%20and%20in%20society%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20very%20open%20with%20Arhant%20and%20everybody%20else%20about%20his%20ADHD%2C%20right%20from%20the%20beginning.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20empowering.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20very%20clear%20with%20him%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20some%20free%20pass%20we%20use%20to%20get%20away%20with%20anything.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20touch%20of%20humour%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20not%20something%20to%20give%20up%20on%20%E2%80%94%20like%20oh%20I%20have%20diabetes%2C%20so%20I%20might%20as%20well%20eat%20%3Cem%3Egulab%20jamuns%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20die%E2%80%A6It%E2%80%99s%20something%20we%20deal%20with%20and%20manage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShelja%20recalls%20being%20a%20young%20mother%20facing%20the%20dreaded%20PTMs%20that%20every%20parent%20of%20a%20neurodivergent%20child%20identifies%20with.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20kept%20telling%20me%20how%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20everything%20wrong.%20I%20asked%20them%20to%20pause%20and%20tell%20me%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20right%2C%20because%20I%20refuse%20to%20accept%20otherwise.%20We%20have%20to%20be%20very%20strong%20advocates%20for%20our%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDoing%20away%20with%20labels%20and%20embracing%20some%20PQ!%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShelja%20says%20her%20personal%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20both%20as%20a%20partner%20to%20her%20husband%2C%20Children%20First%20co-founder%20Dr%20Amit%20Sen%2C%20and%20as%20mother%20to%20a%20son%20with%20ADHD%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20her%20have%20%E2%80%9Can%20easy%20relationship%20with%20the%20diagnosis%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%