80%99am%3F%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20I%20tell%20them%20it%20is%20not%20their%20need%20to%20learn%20ABCD%20%E2%80%94%20that%20might%20be%20your%20need.%20For%20them%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20most%20likely%20to%20make%20some%20friends%2C%20have%20some%20fun%2C%20play.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Priya%20began%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F353745%2Fakash-muralidharan-masterchef-tamil-winner-vizha-medai-south-indian-food-adhd-ravioli-rasam-pongal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20learning%20about%20ADHD%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20support%20Arhant%2C%20pop-its%20and%20fidget%20spinners%20appeared%20all%20over%20the%20house.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20about%20providing%20the%20right%20environment%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManju%20shares%20how%20Lavanya%20still%20treasures%20something%20many%20children%20today%20have%20lost%20%E2%80%94%20colony%20playtime%20in%20the%20evenings.%20She%20also%20smiles%2C%20Manju%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9COnly%20meaningful%20smiles%2C%20not%20social%20smiles.%E2%80%9D%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20distinction%20that%20stays%20with%20me%20%E2%80%94%20a%20small%20reminder%20of%20how%20the%20simplest%20human%20connections%20can%20be%20the%20most%20transformative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHope%2C%20policy%20and%20the%20path%20ahead%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F417965%2Fmilan-singh-autism-awareness-motherhood-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emothers%20lead%20the%20charge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20responsibility%20is%20shared%20by%20all.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20heal%20in%20kinships%2C%20not%20in%20silos%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shelja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20the%20shift%20needs%20to%20happen%20%E2%80%94%20a%20collective%20rethinking%20of%20what%20we%20value%20as%20a%20culture%2C%20society%2C%20and%20country.%20She%20invokes%20Thich%20Nhat%20Hanh%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20watering%E2%80%9D%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20all%20have%20positive%20and%20negative%20traits%20like%20seeds%2C%20and%20they%20grow%20depending%20on%20what%20is%20watered.%20If%20we%20keep%20trying%20to%20make%20the%20child%20perfect%20by%20certain%20standards%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20watering%20the%20negative%20seeds.%20The%20same%20applies%20to%20us%20as%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20society%20as%20a%20whole.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShreya%20is%20unequivocal%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20state%20that%20no%20child%20is%20left%20behind%20and%20is%20provided%20the%20environment%20and%20resources%20as%20per%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20needs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20points%20out%20that%20India%20has%20done%20this%20before%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20KV%20system%2C%20while%20poorly%20resourced%2C%20has%20produced%20high%20educational%20standards.%20We%20have%20the%20IITs%20and%20medical%20schools.%20We%20should%20replicate%20those%20models%20at%20the%20primary%20level%20for%20this%20too.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriya%20calls%20for%20%E2%80%9Creal%20value%20training%20at%20all%20levels.%E2%80%9D%20Aditi%20wants%20strong%20policies%20for%20schools%2C%20assisted%20living%20centres%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20insurance%2C%20with%20%E2%80%9Cthose%20with%20lived%20experiences%20at%20the%20policy-making%20tables.%E2%80%9D%20Anita%20envisions%20common%20learning%20resource%20centres%2C%20tied%20to%20NGOs%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20experts%2C%20working%20with%20parents%2C%20children%2C%20and%20educators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%20advocates%20%E2%80%9Cbuilding%20the%20system%20around%20the%20child%2C%E2%80%9D%20not%20fragmenting%20support%20by%20diagnosis%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20talk%20of%20neurodiversity%2C%20the%20child%20should%20be%20at%20the%20centre%20%E2%80%94%20not%20that%20the%20speech%20issue%20child%20goes%20to%20a%20speech%20therapist%2C%20the%20sensory%20needs%20child%20to%20an%20occupational%20therapist%2C%20and%20so%20on.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20has%20a%20role%20too.%20Swaati%20loves%20the%20Korean%20OTT%20series%20%3Cem%3EExtraordinary%20Attorney%20Woo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20portrays%20its%20protagonist%20in%20her%20entirety%2C%20not%20just%20as%20someone%20with%20Asperger%E2%80%99s.%20Aditi%20recalls%20how%20%3Cem%3ETaare%20Zameen%20Par%3C%2Fem%3E%20helped%20India%20understand%20dyslexia%2C%20and%20says%20Much%20Much%20Media%2C%20which%20she%20runs%20with%20co-founder%20Alaap%2C%20aims%20to%20change%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20want%20to%20move%20away%20from%20pity%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Ebechara%3C%2Fem%3E%20(poor%20thing)%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20and%20from%20feel-good%20inspiration%2C%20towards%20authentic%2C%20lived%20experiences.%E2%80%9D%20She%20notes%20that%20representation%20of%20neurodiversity%20is%20shifting%20much%20like%20LGBTQ%2B%20visibility%20once%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnita%20is%20excited%20about%20a%20new%20RCI%20directive%20proposing%20a%20CBSE%20certificate%20programme%20in%20inclusive%20practices%20for%20mainstream%20teachers.%20Shreya%20shares%20a%20hopeful%20note%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20started%20understanding%20intersectionality%2C%20even%20if%20in%20a%20limited%20way%20%E2%80%94%20without%20it%2C%20how%20can%20we%20progress%20as%20a%20society%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20Swaati%20leaves%20me%20with%20a%20question%20that%20could%20guide%20the%20future%3A%20%E2%80%9CLet%E2%80%99s%20just%20ask%20ourselves%2C%20for%20our%20children%2C%20what%20does%20the%20child%20need%20to%20bloom%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20that%20simple.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EListening%20is%20where%20inclusion%20begins%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20think%20back%20to%20the%20moment%20when%20my%20nephew%2C%20still%20in%20that%20post-%3Cem%3ESZP%3C%2Fem%3E%20haze%2C%20tells%20my%20daughter%20about%20his%20friend%E2%80%99s%20brother%20who%20has%20Down%20syndrome.%